5.2 Implementing basic operations (push, pop to front, middle, or back)

In a linked list, you can push and pop elements from the front or the back of the list. To push an element to the front of the list, you can create a new node with the new data, and set the next pointer of the new node to the current head of the list. Then, you can set the head of the list to the new node.

