9.1 Checking for failure when opening a file

When opening a file using a stream, you should check if the file was opened successfully before attempting to read or write to it.

Example:

```
// main.cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>

int main()
{
    std::ifstream file("file.txt");

    if (file.is_open()) {
        std::cout << "File opened successfully" << std::endl;

        // Read from the file
        std::string line;
        while (std::getline(file, line)) {
            std::cout << line << std::endl;
        }

        file.close();
    } else {
        std::cout << "File failed to open" << std::endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```

